The British Petroleum Co PLC (BP.L) oilrefinery at Grangemouth, closed after an explosion and fireeight days ago, is expected to partially reopen next week, arefinery spokesman said.    He said the entire 178,500 bpd refinery has been shut sincethe accident which killed one person and damaged the site'shydrocracker. The main units will resume operation next weekbut the hydrocracker will be closed for an unspecified period.The spokesman said the refinery had been operating at abouthalf its capacity since end-January due to overhaul work onpart of the complex. The overhaul is expected to end by lateApril. REUTER&#3;